{"TopicId":177032,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Mods useful for machinima filmmakers?","CreatedByName":"vger","CreatedById":67603,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-25T04:46:59Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"vger","CreatedById":67603,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-25T04:46:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m looking for anything that will allow for good machinima creation. Things like the ability to record a mission and then play it back while observing from a different \u0022camera.\u0022 A \u0022zoom\u0022 camera to grab footage of a blastoff as if viewed from the planet surface, like the kind of shots we see in live coverage of a rocket launch. A way to ride \u0022shotgun\u0022 near a vessel as it executes maneuvers, staying relative to its movement but still allowing slow pans past it? Any utility that could aid in making cinematic scenes with no trace of the UI. Have things like this been done?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LitaAlto","CreatedById":110917,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-27T00:14:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere isn\u0027t really anything like that.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nMost of us use a tool like KerbCam or Camera Tools for the camera angles, and leverage quicksaves so we can reshoot scenes until we have all the footage we need.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nCamera Tools is my favorite, as you can set a static location for the camera, which is good for ground camera shots,\u00A0or have it move with the craft. You can also\u00A0set autozoom, set relative velocity for those \u0022shotgun\u0022 slow pans you mention, and use the numpad to manually control the camera in any mode. It also has a \u0022dogfight\u0022 mode which is really handy not just for dogfights but for docking maneuvers, EVAs, and any scene where there\u0027s at least two craft. And it has a camera pathing tool, which is handy but not as flexible as the pathing in KerbCam.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe mod is abandoned and hasn\u0027t been updated in a while, but seems to work fine in every version of KSP since.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8063783751\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/84938-105-camera-tools-v151-dogfight-mode-autozoom-margin-slider-march-28/\u0026amp;\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbCam mainly focuses on pathing, and has been kept more up-to-date by volunteers, and if you like the control of pathing, this might be a better option:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/cartman09/kerbcam\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/cartman09/kerbcam\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd for my cinematics, I sometimes create a tiny probe with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E and a few choice\u00A0cameras from Hullcam VDS -- or even EVA a Kerbal and use the same mod for a Kerbal-view shot.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1178703018\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/145633-141-hullcam-vds-continued/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2710247\u0026amp;embedComment=2710247\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2710247\u0022 style=\u0022height:309px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope this helps!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-27T01:01:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223422796\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177032\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221532650475\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110917\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LitaAlto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, LitaAlto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mod is abandoned and hasn\u0027t been updated in a while, but seems to work fine in every version of KSP since.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFYI .... Camera Tools has been kept up to date since the BDAc team was formed over 2 years ago\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2442045984\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/155014-14x-bdarmory-continued-v1221-7102018-vessel-mover-camera-tools-bdmk22-destruction-effects-burn-together/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LitaAlto","CreatedById":110917,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-27T01:03:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223422824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177032\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221532653300\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150019\